dd<br />&gt; another flag that says we want a new empty memory map instead (obviously<br />&gt; this flag cannot be used from user space). Problem solved.<br /><br />Problems also solved by calling "exit_mm()" in the nfsiod. I think it <br />works, but I never actually tested it (I have them compiled in, not as <br />modules).Want to try 1.3.96?<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
